## Project Vision & Context
The **Ar-Ge İnovasyon ve Girişimcilik Kulübü** web platform is the club’s official, public-facing website and members-only workspace.

**Primary goals**
- Publish **announcements / competitions / events** with a clean editorial experience.
- Provide a **Matchmaking & Team Building** marketplace where students can:
  - post a project idea and request teammates (**Team Ads**)
  - apply to existing team ads
  - showcase their skills and portfolios in a unified **Member Profile**

**Non-goals (for early phases)**
- Complex multi-role marketplace (no “employer vs candidate” split).
- Overly decorative UI; the product must feel **premium, minimalist, and fast**.

## Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js (App Router) with TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Animation**: Framer Motion (subtle, premium; no “bouncy” motion)
- **Backend**: Next.js Route Handlers (`app/api/*`)
- **Database**: **PostgreSQL + Prisma**
- **Auth**: (Phase 7+ decision) Auth.js (NextAuth) **or** custom session/JWT (to be implemented incrementally)
- **Validation**: Zod for server-side input validation

## System Architecture
### App structure (high level)
- Public marketing pages (home, announcements index, announcement detail, team ads index, team ad detail)
- Authenticated area (member dashboard, profile, create team ad, applications)
- Admin area (moderation queue, announcements CRUD)

### Database schema overview (minimum viable)
- **User / Member**
  - id, name, email, image
  - bio, department, year
  - skills/tags (many-to-many or array depending on DB strategy)
  - portfolio links (GitHub, LinkedIn, Behance, personal site)
  - role flag for **Admin** vs **Member** (RBAC)
- **Announcement**
  - title, slug, content, publishedAt, priority
- **TeamAd**
  - title, description, requiredSkills/tags, status (Idea/Prototype/Active)
  - moderationState (Pending/Approved/Rejected)
  - ownerMemberId
- **Application**
  - teamAdId, applicantMemberId, message, createdAt, status

### API / Route Handlers
- All write endpoints must:
  - validate input with **Zod**
  - enforce auth & authorization server-side
  - return consistent errors (no leaking stack traces)

## Core Features (MVP path)
- **Announcements/Competitions**
  - Public listing + detail
  - Admin CRUD (create/edit/publish)
- **Matchmaking**
  - Team Ads marketplace with tag filtering
  - Apply flow for members
- **Admin Moderation**
  - Team ads default to **Pending**
  - Admin approves before public listing

## UI/UX & Animation Guidelines
**Design language**
- Premium minimalism: generous whitespace, strict alignment, consistent spacing scale.
- Typography: neutral modern font system, clear hierarchy (H1/H2/body).
- Dark-mode-first or high-contrast theme (decide in Phase 1 setup; keep consistent).

**Motion rules (Framer Motion)**
- Default pattern: subtle **fade + translateY(8–16px)** on enter.
- Duration: ~\(0.25s–0.45s\), easing: `easeOut`-like curves.
- **NEVER** use playful/bouncy presets for core UI.
- Page transitions: simple cross-fade; avoid layout jank.

**Accessibility**
- Keyboard navigable UI, visible focus rings.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (animations must degrade gracefully).

## Security & SEO Requirements
**Security**
- Zero-trust: server validates everything.
- RBAC: Admin-only routes protected in **middleware** and on the server.
- Never commit secrets; use `.env.local`.
- Rate limiting for auth-sensitive and write endpoints (Phase 2+ if needed).

**SEO**
- Semantic HTML, OpenGraph meta for public pages.
- Clean URLs: `/announcements/[slug]`, `/team-ads/[id-or-slug]`.
- Performance: image optimization (`next/image`), avoid heavy JS on public pages.

## Folder Structure (App Router)
- `app/` (routes, layouts)
- `app/(public)/...` and `app/(dashboard)/...` (route groups)
- `app/api/` (route handlers)
- `components/` (shared UI)
- `lib/` (server utilities, auth, db, validation)
- `styles/` (globals if needed)
- `types/` (shared types where appropriate)